Dear Respondent,



 You are invited to take part in a research study being conducted as part of a postgraduate Masters in Management course at Warwick Business School. Before you decide whether to participate, please read the following information carefully to understand what the study involves.


The aim of this study is to explore consumer preferences and decision-making processes when selecting fine dining restaurants. Specifically, the research seeks to examine how factors such as food quality/menu variety, peer perception, ambience, and pricing strategies influence your choices. Your insights will be invaluable in helping us understand these dynamics more deeply, and your participation will contribute significantly to this research.



Your participation will involve completing a 10-minute questionnaire that will be entirely online. The questions will focus on your dining preferences, experiences, and thoughts about various aspects of restaurant selection. Please know that your participation in this study is entirely voluntary. You are free to withdraw at any point without needing to provide a reason, and doing so will have no negative consequences. The study has been approved by the University of Warwick's Ethics Committee.

Your responses will be treated anonymously and in strict accordance with the University of Warwick's data protection policy. At no stage will you be individually identified, your name will not appear in any reports, and any identifiable data collected will be securely destroyed at the conclusion of the project. Your privacy and confidentiality are paramount to us.

Your insights will contribute to shaping future strategies for fine dining restaurants, and your data may be used for related research activities with your consent. For further information or to withdraw from the study, contact Mausam Aktar Mazarbhuiya (Mausam.Mazarbhuiya@warwick.ac.uk) 

Thank you for considering this opportunity to contribute to our research.

If you are happy to proceed and take part in the study, please click the button below to begin the survey. 

 
Do you consent to take part in this survey ?

column47:
Crafting Your Perfect Fine-Dining Experience: A Choice Experiment



In this section, you will be presented with a series of 12 questions, each featuring two different fine-dining restaurant profiles. Each profile represents a different combination of attributes that a fine-dining restaurant might have. Your task is to choose the fine dining restaurant you would most likely dine at based on the provided attributes. These attributes include price, peer recommendations, ambience, and food quality/menu variety. By selecting your preferred fine-dining restaurant profiles, you will help us understand which combinations of attributes are most important to you when choosing a fine-dining restaurant. Please consider each profile carefully and select the one that best matches your preferences. The attributes of the restaurants include :



Price: The cost per person for a meal in the restaurant, which can vary, giving you an idea of affordability.

Peer Recommendation: The source of reviews influencing your restaurant choice. This can include no recommendation, recommendations from a close friend, social media influencer posts, or positive online reviews from strangers.

Ambience: The overall atmosphere and mood of the restaurant, which affect the dining experience.

Food Quality/Menu Variety: The overall standard and diversity of the food options available at the restaurant. This includes the quality of the ingredients, the preparation and presentation of dishes, the variety of different types of dishes offered, and the inclusion of various cuisines and dietary preferences. 

As you make your choices, imagine these attributes influencing your decision in choosing a restaurant.
